{{DISPLAYTITLE:''La Gazelle''}}
'''''La Gazelle''''' is the name of a long-distance [[passenger train]] service operated by the [[Congo–Ocean Railway]]. The train was introduced in 2012.

==Route==
The train runs between [[Brazzaville]] and [[Pointe-Noire railway station|Pointe-Noire]] and stops at 9 intermediate stations along the route. As of January 2014 the journey was scheduled to take either 14 or 16 hours depending on whether the service was overnight or during the day.<ref>{{cite web| title=2014 Timetable| website=Lonely Planet| url=https://www.lonelyplanet.com/thorntree/forums/africa/congo/la-gazelle-train-brazzaville-to-pointe-noire}}</ref>

==Rolling stock==
The train uses Korean manufactured passenger railway cars which include a [[Dining car|restaurant and bar car]] and has its own engine which supplies the cars with electricity for [[air conditioning]] and [[power outlet]]s.<ref>{{cite video| year=2012| title=Extreme Railways: Congos Jungle Railway| url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2xrH6cuoXn4}}</ref><ref>{{cite video| title=Local news report| year=2012| url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b4n8NuW7fOk}}</ref><ref>{{cite video| title=News report video from the start of services| year=2012| url=http://www.dailymotion.com/video/xsrtg1_cfco-le-train-la-gazelle-arrive-a-la-gare-de-brazzaville_news}}</ref>

